Great App. Is it possible to flash a Nrf51822 module using the vesc? Or do you need the STLink? One of the features of the new update is "Can be used to make a custom NRF5x module".
replyContent: It is possible from the desktop version of VESC Tool. You can connect the SWD pins from the VESC to the SWD pins of the NRF5x and and use the VESC as an SWD programmer. This is managed from the SWD Prog page in VESC Tool. Firmwares are included with VESC Tool for the NRF51822, NRF52832 and NRF52840. The RX and RX pins are in the FW name.
